QCS - Quick Creation System

The QCS (Quick Creation System) is an in-game tool for builders to create
and manage rooms, NPCs, weapons, armor, and generic items within their
wizard workspace. It provides simple commands to generate templates,
edit them, and deploy copies into the game world.

Commands:
  qcs create <type> <name>
  qcs modify <name> <field> <value>
  qcs deploy <name> here
  qcs deploy <name> <room>
  qcs list

Create: Generates a starter LPC template file in your workspace for the
specified type (npc, room, weapon, armor, item).

Modify: Edits fields within a created template (descriptions, stats,
exits, damage, etc.) by updating the LPC file.

Deploy: Loads or clones the template into the game world at the specified
location or into your current room.
